title: Dera chief again seeks parole; Give reasons, EC tells Haryana
Two Jaipur heritage sites shut for 2 days to wipe out rodents
HC grants murder accused bail as trial inconclusive after 12 years

description: Two astronauts stuck on the ISS since June finally got their return transport through a SpaceX capsule after NASA deemed Boeing's Starliner unsafe due to thruster failures and helium leaks. The Dragon capsule will remain docked until February, while NASA continues inspecting the Starliner.
title: SpaceX capsule docks at ISS: Nasa astronauts receive ride to get home in '25

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali criticizes the management of Kanpur's Green Park for failing to prepare the ground despite no rain on Sunday. Wet patches delayed play in the India-Bangladesh Test, which could affect India's World Test Championship standings. He suggests suspending future Tests in Kanpur due to inadequate facilities.
title: 'Suspend Test matches in Kanpur': Basit Ali after India-B'desh Day 3 abandoned
BJP expels ex-minister, 7 other rebels in Haryana
India would have offered Pak more aid than IMF if ties were better: Rajnath

description: The Allahabad High Court reprimanded Amroha district magistrate Rajesh Kumar Tyagi for procedural lapses in approving charges under the Gangster Act against three residents. Admitting errors, the state government transferred him. The court granted bail to the accused and quashed their FIRs, citing improper preparation of a gangster chart by local authorities.
title: Amroha DM shifted over Gangster Act lapses
Doctor found dead inside car in UP hospital, needle mark on hand
Join 'Create in India' challenge, be a part of new sectors: PM Modi
Ahead of Mann ki Baat 10th anniv, PM highlights efforts to save water
Life support call to put undue stress on doctors: IMA
Pvt fin firm staff ends life in UP, cites ‘work pressure’ in note
Muzaffarnagar riots: 10 acquitted inmurder case due to ‘lack of evidence’
Govt block on account of ‘Hindutva Watch’ not justified, X tells Delhi HC

description: US President Joe Biden highlighted the necessity of preventing an all-out war in the Middle East amid rising tensions between Israel and Hezbollah. Israeli airstrikes in Lebanon resulted in significant casualties, including Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah's death. The White House supports a 21-day temporary cease-fire proposed by multiple nations during the recent UN General Assembly.
title: 'We really have to avoid it': Biden urges avoidance of all-out war

description: Home Minister Amit Shah announced that the Waqf (Amendment) Bill, 2024, will be passed in the winter session of Parliament. Addressing rallies in Haryana, he promised government jobs with pensions for youths and criticized Congress for spreading misinformation about the Agnipath scheme. The bill aims to enhance transparency in waqf authorities.
title: 'Waqf bill passage soon': Amit Shah sets stage for opposition showdown
North India logs its best monsoon in 11 years

description: Indian researchers found that the global Covid lockdowns of 2020 may have caused an 8-10 Kelvin drop in lunar surface temperatures. This decrease is attributed to reduced Earth's outgoing radiation due to decreased human activity. The study highlights the Moon as an amplifier of Earth's radiation signature, but more data is needed for confirmation.
title: Covid lockdown on earth led to dip in Moon's temperature: Study
Terrorist killed in Kathua gunfight

description: India is set for its fifth winter of troop deployment in eastern Ladakh and Arunachal Pradesh-Sikkim due to ongoing distrust with China. Although political-diplomatic talks indicate some progress, the trust deficit with the PLA remains significant. The Indian Army is transitioning to its winter posture and reviewing the operational situation.
title: India to maintain LAC troop deployment as trust deficit with China remains
Car tails bike-borne cop on patrol, mows him down

description: Two Meitei youths from Thoubal district disappeared after attending a recruitment test in Imphal West, Manipur. Allegedly abducted by Kuki militants, their case has drawn attention from CM N Biren Singh, who is focusing on their rescue. A third youth has been found safe, and efforts are ongoing to locate the remaining two.
title: Manipur CM Biren accuses Kuki militants of abducting 2 Manipuri youths

description: Karan Veer Mehra won Khatron Ke Khiladi 14, outshining Gashmeer Mahajani and Krishna Shroff. He received Rs 20 lakh and a new car as prizes. The finale featured challenging air, water, and helicopter tasks. This season took place in Romania for the first time, adding an exciting twist to the show.
title: Khatron Ke Khiladi 14 winner: Karan Veer Mehra lifts trophy
Govt expands adoption pool for children in child care institutions
Protests in Kashmir over Nasrallah’s killing
Dizziness on J&K dais halts Kharge speech, says won't die before ousting Modi

description: Campaigning for the final phase of J&K assembly elections ended peacefully, covering 40 segments across seven districts with heightened security due to recent terrorist activities. Key candidates include Ajaz Ahmad Guru and Sajad Gani Lone. This election is the first since Article 370's abrogation, featuring fierce competition among BJP, Congress-NC alliance, and PDP.
title: Campaign for J&K’s final phase ends

description: France has presented its final price offer to India for 26 Rafale Marine jets just before Indian NSA Ajit Doval's visit to France. This crucial deal for the Indian Navy includes integrating indigenous radars and weapons. Further discussions are expected during the India-France Strategic Dialogue in Paris.
title: India receives final price offer from France for 26 Rafale Marine jets

description: Pakistan is set to reduce administrative expenditures by cutting 150,000 government jobs and closing six ministries as part of an IMF-backed $7 billion loan deal. Finance Minister Muhammad Aurangzeb stressed the importance of implementing policies to formalize the economy and increase tax revenues, aiming for this to be Pakistan's final IMF program.
title: Crisis-hit Pakistan cuts 150K jobs, dissolves 6 ministries

description: Baramulla MP Sheikh Abdul Rashid's campaign vehicle was attacked in Kupwara district by a man who stomped on the bonnet and broke the windshield. Rashid, inside the car at the time, was unharmed. Sources suggest the attacker is a former aide of Rashid. The motive behind the assault remains unclear.
title: Watch: Engineer Rashid's car attacked in J&K

description: Austria's far-right Freedom Party (FPO), under Herbert Kickl's leadership, has won the general election with 29.1% of the vote. The FPO outpaced Chancellor Karl Nehammer's Austrian People's Party (OVP). The party's focus on immigration and economic issues tapped into public frustration over inflation, the Ukraine war, and migration concerns. Kickl needs a coalition partner to govern.
title: In a first, Putin-friendly far-right Freedom Party wins Austria elections

description: Shiv Sena (UBT) chief Uddhav Thackeray alleges that Union home minister Amit Shah instructed BJP leaders to politically target him and NCP leader Sharad Pawar during a private meeting. Thackeray emphasizes that his political future will be decided by the people, urging voters to support the Maha Vikas Aghadi in upcoming elections.
title: 'Told BJP leaders to break ...' : Uddhav's big charge against Amit Shah

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi reached out to Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge to check on his health after he became unwell during a rally in J&K's Kathua. After being briefly hospitalized, Kharge declared his intent to keep fighting politically against PM Modi. His son later assured that Kharge is recovering well.
title: PM Modi dials Mallikarjun Kharge after he falls ill at a rally in J&K

description: Donald Trump escalated his rhetoric against Kamala Harris, labeling her 'mentally impaired' and calling for her disqualification. He accused her of letting foreign criminals into the country to win elections. The Harris campaign hit back, calling Trump a 'loser' for avoiding a second debate. This development adds tension to an already contentious election season.
title: Trump says Harris is 'mentally impaired' and should be disqualified

description: Asteroid '2024 PT5', discovered by ATLAS in August, flew past Earth on September 29 and will orbit it for 57 days. This mini-moon, part of the Arjuna asteroid group, is closely monitored by ISRO's NETRA. It will leave Earth's orbit on November 25 and is expected to return in 2055.
title: Earth gets a ‘mini moon’ for 2 months and it has a Mahabharata connection

description: The Israeli Defense Forces have uncovered and dismantled a one-kilometre Hamas tunnel in Gaza as part of their operations to free hostages and weaken Hamas. The conflict has expanded since October 7, 2023, involving Hezbollah in Lebanon and Houthi rebels in Yemen, resulting in significant casualties and widespread displacement.
title: Israel uncovers 1km Hamas tunnel network in Gaza

description: The Israeli military confirmed that an airstrike in Beirut killed Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah and over 20 other members. The attack targeted underground headquarters beneath civilian buildings. This has led to heightened tensions, with Iran calling for a UN Security Council meeting to discuss Israel's recent actions in Lebanon.
title: Body of Hezbollah leader recovered from bombed site

description: The BCCI has announced new retention rules for the IPL 2025 season, sparking debate over Dhoni's future. Bollywood star Shah Rukh Khan humorously commented on Dhoni's potential retirement at the IIFA awards. Under the new rules, Dhoni qualifies as an uncapped player, allowing CSK to retain him for a reduced price.
title: 'Na na karke 10 baar IPL khel jaate hai': SRK's MS Dhoni remark

description: Nitin Edwin Michael, a senior analyst at HCL Technologies Ltd., suffered a fatal cardiac arrest at the company's Nagpur office. Found unresponsive in the washroom, he received emergency care before being taken to AIIMS Nagpur where he was declared dead. HCLTech expressed deep sorrow and is supporting his family while emphasizing their healthcare initiatives for employees.
title: HCLTech employee dies after cardiac arrest at Nagpur office

description: The contest to replace Rishi Sunak as Conservative leader intensifies, with immigration at the forefront. Leading candidates Robert Jenrick and Kemi Badenoch push for stricter Indian visa rules and stress cultural integration. The Conservative Party conference in Birmingham will be pivotal as candidates present their visions ahead of the final vote on November 2.
title: Sunak on way out? Focus on Indian visas as Tories mull leadership change

description: Protests are ongoing against burying Akshay Shinde, accused of sexually abusing two girls and recently killed in a police encounter, in Ulhasnagar. Shiv Sena and BJP workers demand that his body not be buried there. Despite a High Court directive to proceed with the burial, tensions persist with significant police presence.
title: Badlapur case accused buried amid protests in Ulhasnagar

description: Razzak Baloch from the Baloch Human Rights Council condemned Pakistan and China for exploiting resources in Balochistan during a protest in Geneva. He demanded their removal to ensure peace for the people of Balochistan, Sindh, and Pashtunistan. He accused both nations of human rights violations and resource exploitation, calling Pakistan a failed state.
title: Pakistan a failed state, China dictating actions: Baloch activist

description: Harry Brook from England made history by scoring 312 runs in a bilateral ODI series against Australia, overtaking Indian cricket stars Virat Kohli and MS Dhoni. His crucial knock of 72 off 52 balls helped England post a total of 308 runs in the final ODI. This achievement marks the highest run tally by any captain in such contests.
title: New Milestone! Brook surpasses Kohli, Dhoni...

description: Nitin Edwin Michael, a senior analyst at HCL Technologies Ltd., suffered a fatal cardiac arrest at the company's Nagpur office. Found unresponsive in the washroom, he received emergency care before being taken to AIIMS Nagpur where he was declared dead. HCLTech expressed deep sorrow and is supporting his family while emphasizing their healthcare initiatives for employees.
title: HCLTech employee dies after cardiac arrest at Nagpur office

description: Delhi Police are investigating the deaths of a man and his four daughters in Vasant Kunj, southwest Delhi, for possible links to occult practices. Red threads found on the girls and other suspicious items have raised concerns. The police will examine similarities with the 2018 Burari suicide case involving 11 family members.
title: Burari 2.0? Cops to probe 'occult' angle in Delhi deaths
J&K cop Bashir Ahmed guns down terrorist before succumbing to injuries

description: Erika Diarte-Carr, a 33-year-old mother from Utah, faces a terminal diagnosis of Stage 4 small cell lung carcinoma and Cushing Syndrome. With just three months left, she has raised over $840,000 through GoFundMe for her children's future. Erika plans to spend her remaining time creating lasting memories with her kids.
title: Why a mom of 2 is busy planning her own funeral

description: In five weeks, daylight saving time will conclude, granting US citizens an additional hour of sleep. This twice-yearly clock adjustment aims to provide more daylight during specific seasons but remains a contentious issue. Currently observed from the second Sunday in March to the first Sunday in November, some lawmakers are contemplating its permanent cessation.
title: Daylight saving time 2024 to end in November: What is it and its history

description: Rohit Sharma spoke about his fitness and career longevity as he nears the milestone of 500 international matches for India. Emphasizing dedication and discipline, he attributed his success to a strict routine focused on fitness, mental well-being, and preparation. Rohit is set to become the fifth Indian cricketer to achieve this feat.
title: Rohit silences fitness critics, says not a lot of cricketers...

description: Prashant Kishor launched an attack on Bihar CM Nitish Kumar, alleging he runs the state under the influence of four retired bureaucrats. Vowing to remove Kumar in the 2025 assembly polls, Kishor highlighted issues like liquor prohibition, land surveys, and smart meters. He aims for a comprehensive victory with his party Jan Suraj.
title: Nitish Kumar has changed, in grip of 4 retired 'babus': Prashant Kishor

description: The Bad Blood Premium Live Event will showcase a Hell in a Cell match between Drew McIntyre and CM Punk. The article revisits the top five greatest moments in Hell in a Cell history, featuring legendary matches with Triple H, Cactus Jack, Undertaker, Edge, Mankind, Shawn Michaels, and Kane that have defined WWE's most brutal encounters.
title: Top 5 greatest hell in cell moments in WWE history

description: Vaani CEO Tushar S's LinkedIn post about co-founder Abhinash's demanding work schedule has triggered a debate on hustle culture.
title: Startup CEO reveals ‘no water…work’ routine; internet says ‘new toxic culture’

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah alleged that 'Pakistan Zindabad' slogans were raised at Congress events and questioned Rahul Gandhi's silence. He criticized Congress for its stance on Article 370, asserting it can't be restored. Shah highlighted BJP's achievements in Haryana, including increased MSP for crops and substantial financial assistance compared to the UPA government.
title: 'Pakistan Zindabad slogans raised': Amit Shah's big charge against Congress

description: The BCCI has set new guidelines for the upcoming IPL mega auction, allowing teams to retain up to six players. Ajay Jadeja recommended that Mumbai Indians keep Rohit Sharma, Jasprit Bumrah, and Suryakumar Yadav while using the Right to Match card for Hardik Pandya. The auction budget will rise to Rs 120 crore.
title: Hardik not in Jadeja's retention list for MI

description: Hezbollah chief Sayyed Hassan Nasrallah was killed in an Israeli airstrike on his underground headquarters in Beirut, following intelligence from an Iranian mole. This operation represents a significant blow to Hezbollah amid heightened conflict with Israel, resulting in substantial casualties on both sides.
title: Tip from mole ...: How high-stakes op to eliminate Hezbollah chief unfolded

description: Cyber Police Kashmir has issued a warning to social media users to avoid sharing content that may incite communal tensions following the killing of Hezbollah chief Hassan Nasrallah by Israeli airstrikes. The advisory emphasises potential legal consequences for provocative posts. Protests have occurred in Shia-majority areas but remain peaceful, with authorities vigilant about social media's impact.
title: Cyber Police Kashmir warns against inflammatory posts over Nasrallah's death

description: During the second Test between India and Bangladesh at Kanpur's Green Park Stadium, poor facilities, especially the drainage system, came under fire. Despite no rain on Day 3, play was abandoned due to a wet outfield, frustrating fans and experts. Questions arise about the venue's suitability for future international matches.
title: 'Itni ghatiya services': Viral video exposes IND vs BAN venue

description: Udhayanidhi Stalin has been elevated to deputy chief minister of Tamil Nadu. Senthil Balaji, who was recently released on bail, is reinstated as a minister. The cabinet reshuffle saw three ministers dropped and three new faces inducted. Higher education minister K Ponmudy has taken over as Forest Minister.
title: TN cabinet reshuffle: Udhayanidhi is dy CM, Senthil Balaji back as minister

description: RP Singh advises Royal Challengers Bengaluru to prioritize retaining Virat Kohli for the IPL 2025 auction. He suggests using the RTM card to reacquire players like Mohammed Siraj and Rajat Patidar. Singh emphasizes building the team around Kohli due to his significant contributions and value to the franchise.
title: 'Retain Kohli, release...': Ex-India pacer's piece of advice for RCB

description: Defence Minister Rajnath Singh said India would have given Pakistan more financial aid than the IMF if relations were friendly. Speaking in Gurez, he stressed India's commitment to Jammu and Kashmir's development, criticized Pakistan for funding terrorism, and promised local recruitment and infrastructure improvements.
title: 'Would have given more than IMF if ...': What Rajnath said on aid to Pak

description: A terrorist was killed in an ongoing operation in Jammu and Kashmir's Kathua district, increasing the death toll to two. The search operation began on Saturday after reports of foreign terrorists in the area. Security forces continue efforts to neutralize remaining threats while ensuring safety for upcoming elections with tight security measures.
title: One terrorist killed in encounter with security forces in J&K's Kathua

description: Delhi CM Atishi met with all ministers to discuss stalled projects and damaged roads after former CM Arvind Kejriwal expressed concerns about delays. A comprehensive review of 1,400 km of PWD roads was conducted. The government is committed to resuming halted projects and improving Delhi's infrastructure.
title: Delhi CM Atishi holds meeting with all ministers, focuses on stalled projects in city

description: Day three of the second India-Bangladesh Test in Kanpur saw no play due to a wet outfield from overnight rain. Bangladesh were at 107/3 in their first innings, with no action on days two and three. India leads the series after securing a win in the first Test held in Chennai.
title: IND vs BAN 2nd Test: Day 3 washed out due to wet outfield in Kanpur

description: Israel has killed Nabil Kaouk, a senior Hezbollah commander, in an airstrike following the death of leader Hassan Nasrallah. Kaouk served as deputy head of Hezbollah’s Central Council and was involved in military operations since the 1980s. Israel has increased its attacks on Hezbollah targets recently, including communication systems and various locations across Lebanon.
title: Who was Nabil Kaouk, top Hezbollah commandar killed by Israel

description: Newly discovered footage capturing President John F Kennedy's motorcade speeding to a Dallas hospital after his fatal wounding has sold for $137,500 at auction. Recorded by Dale Carpenter Sr on November 22, 1963, the film reveals the urgency and heartbreak of that day. The buyer remains anonymous.
title: Rare JFK speeding motorcade footage sells for $137,500 at auction

description: Wrestling manager Jim Cornette has expressed strong disapproval of Jey Uso's gimmick and in-ring performance despite Uso’s recent win over Bron Breakker on RAW for the Intercontinental Championship. Cornette called Jey’s character his least favorite among current top stars, even as fans continue to cheer for Jey’s solo career.
title: 'I hate it. I hate 'Yeet.' - A WWE veteran revealed that he dislikes Jey Uso

description: Haryana's job crisis is causing a surge in illegal migration as young men from villages like Durana risk dangerous 'donkey routes' to the US. Limited local employment and shrinking landholdings drive this trend, leading many to risk severe consequences for better opportunities abroad despite legal repercussions.
title: Jobless Haryana pays fortune for donkeys, flees to war zones

description: The Israeli military executed airstrikes on multiple Hezbollah targets in Lebanon, targeting weapon storage and military infrastructure. This follows the killing of Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah. Prime Minister Netanyahu vows to persist until securing the Lebanese border. The conflict has resulted in significant casualties and displacement within Lebanon.
title: Footage shows how Israel carried out raids on 'dozens' of Hezbollah targets
Watch: Kharge falls ill while delivering speech on stage, takes jab at PM Modi

description: Shashi Negi, an apple trader from Shimla, was apprehended for running an interstate drug racket involving 'chitta' (adulterated heroin). Orders were placed via WhatsApp and delivered through a complex network to avoid detection. Police connected him to Nigerian and other gangs, seizing 465 grams of drugs and arresting 25 associates.
title: 'Order on WhatsApp': How police unearthed interstate drug racket run by apple trader

description: Palak Sindhwani, who portrayed Sonu Bhide in Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah, has announced her departure from the show after five years. She accuses the producers of mental harassment and pressuring her for brand details and payments. Palak claims they delayed her resignation process and issued a legal notice when she decided to quit.
title: Taarak Mehta's actor Palak Sindhwani reveals she suffered panic attacks

description: The FIFA World Cup has highlighted exceptional goal scorers like Miroslav Klose, Ronaldo, Gerd Müller, Just Fontaine, and Lionel Messi. These football legends have set impressive scoring records across multiple tournaments, playing pivotal roles in their teams' successes and etching their names into the annals of football World Cup history.
title: Top Five FIFA World Cup Goal Scorers: From Klose to Messi

description: Virat Kohli's exceptional performances against Australia, especially in ODIs, are well-known. He excels in high-pressure chases and has scored significant centuries on Australian soil. His rivalry with players like James Faulkner adds intensity to these encounters. Kohli's aggressive and competitive nature fuels his iconic performances, making this rivalry a highlight of modern cricket.
title: 'Smashed you enough...': When Virat silenced Faulkner with a savage reply

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi thanked listeners as his 'Mann Ki Baat' radio programme marked its 10th anniversary. He highlighted several community-driven initiatives, such as environmental campaigns and language preservation efforts. Modi also mentioned the return of ancient artifacts from the US and celebrated the successes of the 'Make in India' campaign.
title: 'Mann ki Baat' completes 10 years: Top quotes from PM Modi's address

description: A farmer couple from Karimnagar district displayed rare generosity by donating 1.06 acres of their land to the local gram panchayat in memory of their youngest son who died in an accident 20 years ago. Valued at Rs 1 crore, this land will benefit the village, and a bust of their son has been erected on it.
title: Telangana couple donate Rs 1 crore land to panchayat in son's memory

description: Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath highlighted that those who formerly criticized India and questioned its sovereignty are now greeting people with 'Ram Ram'. During election rallies in Haryana, he asserted that a stronger BJP would result in even opponents of Ram and Shri Krishna temples chanting 'Hare Rama, Hare Krishna' on the streets.
title: Those who opposed India now greet with Ram-Ram: UP CM Yogi

description: Rohit Sharma, captain of the Indian cricket team, acknowledges the perpetual expectations from fans and experts. Renowned for his ability to score big hundreds and maintain composure under pressure, Rohit is expected to lead India with tactical acumen while upholding high fitness standards. His performance in ICC tournaments remains pivotal for India's success.
title: 'Sharmaji ka ladka...': Rohit on why expectations are important in life

description: ​Gladwell compared Harvard's admissions process with that of Caltech, a university with a merit-based approach. He observed that the proportion of Asian-American students at Caltech rose significantly, from 25% to 43% between 1992 and 2013. Meanwhile, Harvard's percentage remained between 15-20%, a disparity he attributed to legacy admissions, donor contributions, and athletic scholarships. Indian applicants, Gladwell added, would find it even harder to get into Ivy leagues.
title: Harvard and anti-Indian bias: Why Ivy leagues have an Asian-American problem

description: WhatsApp executives face legal action in Gurugram for not providing requested information to local police. Despite multiple requests, WhatsApp failed to comply, leading to accusations of aiding the accused individuals.
title: Gurugram Police files case against WhatsApp directors and nodal officers: Here’s why

description: A Delhi Police constable lost his life in a road rage incident in Nangloi after requesting a driver to move his car. He was dragged for 10 meters before being hit by another vehicle. The car involved has been seized, but the driver is currently on the run. Investigation continues.
title: Delhi Police constable crushed to death by 'liquor supplier'

description: Amitabh Bachchan is set to receive a special birthday surprise on Kaun Banega Crorepati 16, with Aamir Khan and his son Junaid Khan making a guest appearance. This celebration marks Bachchan's 82nd birthday on October 11. The episode is scheduled to air at 9 PM on Sony Entertainment Television.
title: Kaun Banega Crorepati 16 Promo: Aamir Khan and son Junaid to make an appearance

description: 'Devara: Part 1', directed by Koratala Siva and featuring Jr. NTR, was released globally on September 27. Despite receiving mixed reviews, the film achieved significant box office success, grossing over Rs 140 crore worldwide on its opening day and surpassing Rs 220 crore within two days, indicating a strong audience response.
title: 'Devara' box office collection day 2: Jr.NTR starrer zooms past Rs 200 crore

description: The IPL Governing Council has reintroduced the 'uncapped player' rule, allowing Chennai Super Kings to retain MS Dhoni as an uncapped player. Dhoni, who retired from international cricket in 2020, played his last international match in 2019. Dhoni had also stepped down from captaincy before IPL 2024 began, handing it over to batsman Ruturaj Gaikwad.
title: CSK can now retain Dhoni, but is he up for another IPL season?

description: Severe flooding in northern and central Bihar follows a major water release from the Birpur barrage on the Kosi River after torrential rains. Over 16 lakh people are affected, with submerged railway tracks and closed roadways. Relief efforts are underway as further heavy rainfall is predicted, exacerbating the situation.
title: Bihar flood: Railway tracks submerged, water enters homes

description: A federal judge has denied Apple's plea for an extension to produce documents concerning recent App Store changes, upholding a September 30 deadline. Apple is required to review and produce over 1.3 million documents in its ongoing legal dispute with Epic Games, which challenges Apple's compliance with a court order on payment policies.
title: Judge ‘warns’ Apple: Your Homework deadline is Monday, September 30, no matter what

description: The Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) has filed a petition in the Supreme Court challenging a recent standing committee election by the Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD), citing violations of the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act. The BJP alleges that AAP is attempting to divert attention from its electoral loss and internal disunity. The dispute over election legality continues.
title: AAP moves Supreme Court against MCD standing committee poll results

description: Gurgaon police have filed an FIR against senior officials of WhatsApp for failing to cooperate in a financial cheating investigation involving The Commodity Hub. The company reported unauthorized transfers amounting to Rs 4 crore. Despite multiple requests, WhatsApp has not provided necessary details about phone numbers linked to the fraud, affecting the probe.
title: Police file FIR against WhatsApp officials for not cooperating in investigation

description: Microsoft has introduced security improvements to its Recall AI feature following concerns about hacker exploitation. Users can now filter data collection, use biometric authentication, and ensure sensitive data is encrypted and stored locally. The upgraded version of Recall will be available in beta next month for Copilot+ PCs, with businesses needing to opt-in.
title: Microsoft VP after company upgrades this AI feature

description: In Chhattisgarh's Bijapur district, five security personnel sustained injuries from a pressure IED explosion planted by Naxalites during a demining operation. The incident took place near the Tarrem police station area. After receiving initial treatment, the injured were transferred to Bijapur district hospital, where their condition is reported as stable.
title: 5 cops injured as IED planted by Naxals explode in Chhattisgarh's Bijapur
Zoon to zyeun: How Iltija Mufti's PDP slogan has been adopted by NC

description: Punjab Chief Minister Bhagwant Mann has tested positive for leptospirosis and is currently receiving treatment at a private hospital in Mohali. He was admitted with inflammation in the pulmonary artery, which affected his heart and blood pressure. Doctors report that his condition is stable, showing significant improvement, but he remains under observation for further medical evaluation.
title: Punjab CM Bhagwant Mann infected with leptospirosis

description: A state food safety team inspected prasad and sweet shops near the Trinetra Ganesh temple in Ranthambore tiger reserve, uncovering 3,470 kg of mouldy laddus. The spoiled sweets were destroyed, and samples sent for adulteration testing. Legal action is anticipated if the laddus are found unsafe for human consumption.
title: 3.4K kg mouldy laddus destroyed at Rajasthan's Trinetra Ganesh temple
Floods, landslides kill 112 people in Nepal

description: A tragic accident occurred in Maihar district when a passenger bus rammed into a stationary truck on National Highway 30, resulting in nine deaths, including a child. The crash took place around 11.30 pm as the bus was en route from Prayagraj to Nagpur. Twenty passengers sustained injuries and are being treated at local hospitals.
title: 9 killed, over 20 injured in bus-truck collision in MP's Maihar

description: A Mumbai-based eye surgeon performed an operation on a blind man from Lahore at an eye hospital in Colombo due to visa issues preventing treatment in India. With help from a local surgeon, the operation restored partial vision within 48 hours. The patient had been unable to see his family for four years.
title: Pakistan patient, Indian doctor and eye operation in Sri Lanka

description: Yemen's Houthi rebels fired a missile at Israel's Ben Gurion Airport, targeting the Israeli Prime Minister after attending the UNGA meeting. This marks their second attack in two days following Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah's death in an Israeli airstrike. International leaders call for ceasefires and diplomatic solutions to avoid further escalation.
title: Missiles fired at Israel from Yemen and Lebanon in response to Hezbollah leader Nasrallah's death: Top developments

description: The IPL Governing Council has announced new regulations for the 2025-27 season, featuring an increased salary cap and the introduction of match fees. Franchises will have an auction purse of INR 120 crore, while players will earn INR 7.5 Lakhs per match in addition to their contracted amounts, enhancing overall player earnings.
title: EXPLAINED: Franchise purse for IPL auction and the new 'match fee'

description: Israeli leaders had been aware of Hassan Nasrallah's location for months and chose to strike this past week due to a limited window of opportunity. Over 80 bombs were dropped in the attack, resulting in the deaths of Nasrallah and Ali Karaki, a top Hezbollah commander. The operation was planned amid cease-fire discussions with American counterparts.
title: Months of intelligence, a few minutes of bombs: How Israel killed Nasrallah

description: Dell has mandated that its global sales team return to the office five days a week starting September 30. The company argues that in-person collaboration will enhance productivity and competitiveness. This move has sparked discontent among employees, who worry about its impact on their work-life balance and speculate it may be an attempt to encourage resignations.
title: Dell ends work from home for global sales team: Read what the company said
HP Congress chief backs her minister son over vendors' name order
30 yrs on, Guj court acquits 3 accused of spreading terror in post-Babri riots
Illegal land hoarding hurt development in the hills: U'khand CM Dhami

description: Rosie Duffield resigned from the Labour Party, accusing Prime Minister Keir Starmer of hypocrisy for accepting gifts while cutting winter heating payments for pensioners. She criticized his policies as inconsistent with Labour values. The controversy has caused friction within the party, especially during their first conference since regaining power.
title: Labour MP Rosie Duffield resigns, accuses UK PM Starmer of 'hypocrisy'
FIR against FM Sitharaman over poll bonds 'extortion', Cong seeks ouster
City in fear: Now, shots fired at hotel, sweet shop

description: In Rangpuri, southwest Delhi, Heeralal Sharma and his four daughters were found dead in their flat. The family had withdrawn socially after Sharma's wife passed away a year ago. Police suspect poisoning and are exploring possible religious or occult motives behind the incident.
title: Man, 4 daughters in their 20s found dead at South Delhi home
Government unveils draft rules to take terminally ill off life support

description: The BCCI announced new IPL Player Regulations for 2025-27, mandating overseas player registration in the 'Big Auction'. Players opting out after being picked at the auction will face a two-season ban. Franchises can retain up to six players, with specific guidelines on capped and uncapped players. The auction is expected in November at an overseas location.
title: BCCI cautions players in IPL Player Regulations 2025-27

description: Rohit Sharma retired from T20 Internationals following India's T20 World Cup victory in June this year. He says he felt it was the right moment to step aside and concentrate on other formats, giving younger players a chance. Rohit, who played 159 T20Is, stressed that fitness is largely mental and he remains capable of playing all formats.
title: Rohit Sharma: 'Only reason I retired from T20Is is...'

description: India's first Oxygen Bird Park near Jamtha in Nagpur has been inaugurated by Union minister Nitin Gadkari. Developed by NHAI over 8 hectares with more than 8,000 plant species, it features natural lakes and jogging tracks. The park aims to promote biodiversity and combat pollution while serving as an eco-tourist destination.
title: India's 1st oxygen bird park opens its wings in Maharashtra

description: Five family members were discovered dead in a New Delhi building, leaving neighbors stunned. Described as reclusive, the family had minimal interaction with others. The mysterious circumstances surrounding their deaths have caused fear and confusion within the community, highlighting how hidden struggles can exist even in crowded neighborhoods.
title: Delhi Rangpuri deaths: All 5 lived a solitary life, neighbours in shock

description: In Rangpuri, investigators are baffled by the deaths of a father and his four differently-abled daughters. Key evidence includes poison packets, a box of sweets, and sacred threads tied around their bodies. Police are considering financial struggles and possible occult rituals as motives while examining CCTV footage for more clues.
title: Sweets, poison & threads: Cops try to connect dots in Delhi Rangpuri deaths

description: Heeralal Sharma, once a supportive family man, became reclusive after his wife's death. His four daughters, who excelled academically, also withdrew from social interactions. Despite attempts by relatives to reach out, Heeralal and his daughters remained isolated. The family's struggles intensified after the mother's passing, leading to tragic consequences.
title: Delhi’s Rangpuri horror: How tragedy turned loving father into stranger

description: In 2018, New Delhi's Burari witnessed a family of 11 committing mass suicide due to Lalit Bhatia's delusions. Currently, police are probing a similar incident in Rangpuri involving five family members. Unlike Burari, where diaries provided insights, investigators now rely on interviews with relatives and neighbors to piece together the story.
title: Delhi's Rangpuri daughter deaths stir memories of Burari horror

description: The Tamil Nadu government has prohibited the breeding of 11 exotic dog breeds due to unsuitable weather conditions and high maintenance needs. Activists urge enforcement of neutering existing banned dogs. The new policy includes guidelines to curb animal abuse by backyard breeders and promotes better care for native dog breeds.
title: Tamil Nadu bans 11 exotic dog breeds, but mum on stopping breeding

description: In Kelambakkam, two men wearing helmets snatched a nine sovereign gold chain worth about 4.8 lakh from a school teacher after one of them held her daughter at knifepoint. The police are investigating and searching for the suspects, trying to obtain CCTV footage from nearby shops to track them down.
title: Two men wearing helmets hold girl at knifepoint, rob mom in Tamil Nadu
